         <abstract>
            <p>The Drazin inverse of a lower Hessenberg matrix is considered. If A is a singular lower Hessenberg matrix, and ai,i+1 ≠ 0, i = 1,2, ···, n — 1, then AD can be given, and expressed explicitly by elements of A. The structure of the Drasin inverse of a lower Hessenberg matrix is also studied.</p>
